/AngularJS and Bootstrap Web Parts Docum.Name: Home.aspx

ListItemFieldValues.Value:
​​​​​​​​​​Getting Started with IQ Parts using AngularJS and Bootstrap

This is a sample from InstantQuick that was created using IQApp Central​. It is a framework that allows for user configurable Web Parts built using SharePopint, AngularJS 1.4 and Bootstrap 3​. ​This sample contains two Web Parts, six sample apps, an extensible configuration system, a template to help you get started with your own apps, and some handy functions to make integrating with SharePoint pages and services easy​.

​​​Two W​eb Parts

There are two Web Parts. One is based on the standard Content Editor Web Part, and the other is based on the Page Viewer Web Part. They are functionally equivalent but the one based on the Page Viewer Web Part​ is slightly easier to use. We built both for comparison purposes, but in the end couldn't really tell a difference. We included both for the sake of completeness. There are two pages that show these Web Parts in action, [[Angular Content Editor IQPart Example]] and Angular PageViewer IQParts Example​​. Each contains three instances of the corresponding Web Part with a nice layout and three of the sample apps.



​​​Six Sample Apps​​​​​

To add ​a sample app to a page, add one of the Web Parts to a page and select an app.


​​​​​Timer and Greeting

These samples are the same app with different configurations. The app itself is the template used if you select Create a new AngularJS app​. These samples demonstrate:

  • ​​Resizing
  • Web Part Configuration forms
  • Using the SharePoint Client Object Model with an AngularJS factory

​Bootstrap Reference

​This simple sample demonstrates the use of a number of Bootstrap styles and components.

​​AngularJS Samples

​These samples are from the AngularJS home page.

​The Basics​

​This is the 'The Basics' sample from https://angularjs.org/​. It demonstrates basic model binding.​

​​​Ad​d Some Control

​This is the 'Add Some Control​' sample from https://angularjs.org/​. It demonstrates the use of controllers and basic forms.

Create Components

​This is the 'Create Components​' sample from https://angularjs.org/​​. It demonstrates the use of directives.

​​​​Create a New AngularJS App

​
To create a new app, add one of the Web Parts to a page and select Create new AngularJS app...​, then give your app a name and description. This will create a new folder in IQAppCore/SPAs with the name you provide and copy the template files for your new app. Edit the files as desired to build your own amazing creation!
